# Commit Convention

All commits must follow **Conventional Commits v1.0**.

## Format

```
<type>(<optional scope>): <short description>

[optional body — explain WHY, not WHAT]
```

## Allowed Types

| Type | When to use |
|------|-------------|
| `feat` | New feature or visible behaviour |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |
| `a11y` | Accessibility improvement (project-local extension) |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `chore` | Tooling, config, dependencies |
| `refactor` | Code restructure without behaviour change |
| `test` | Adding or fixing tests |
| `style` | Formatting, whitespace (no logic change) |

## Scopes (optional but recommended)

`cv`, `layout`, `component`, `print`, `config`, `deps`, `ci`

## Rules

- Subject line ≤ 72 characters, imperative mood ("add" not "added").
- No period at the end of the subject line.
- Breaking changes: add `!` after the type (`feat!:`) and explain in the body.
- Reference issues in the footer: `Closes #12`.

## Examples

```
feat(cv): add publications section from cv.json
fix(print): prevent page break inside experience entries
perf(images): convert hero to WebP with srcset
a11y(nav): add skip-to-content link
chore(deps): upgrade astro to 4.8.0
```
